# MemoCloud - Personal Knowledge Base with RAG

**Demo:** https://memocloud.io

## Core Concept
A "second brain" where you can upload documents, bookmarks, and notes — then search using natural language (semantic search) and get AI-assisted answers backed by your own knowledge.

---

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend:** Next.js 15 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- **AI/ML:** OpenAI (embeddings + GPT)
- **RAG Framework:** LangChain
- **Vector DB:** ChromaDB (local)
- **File Processing:** pdf-parse, mammoth (DOCX)

## Data Model

```typescript
interface Memo {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  content: string;
  source: 'upload' | 'bookmark' | 'note';
  url?: string;
  fileType?: string;
  category: string;
  folder: string;
  subfolder?: string;
  createdAt: Date;
}
```

## UI
- Dark theme (#0a0a0f background)
- Sidebar with folder tree
- Search bar + folder navigation
- Search results: title, URL/source, datetime below

## Features
1. Create memo (upload PDF/DOCX, bookmark URL, or note)
2. Folder tree navigation
3. Semantic search (embeddings)
4. RAG query mode with GPT-4

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Can create memo with title + folder
- [ ] Can upload PDF/DOCX files
- [ ] Can add bookmark (URL)
- [ ] Can write free-text note
- [ ] Folder tree displays and navigates
- [ ] Search returns results with title, URL, datetime
- [ ] Semantic search works by meaning
- [ ] RAG mode feeds context to LLM
